<TEXT>  Top 10 runners-up:; 1. Chemists make carbon molecules, called
"buckminsterfullerenes," shaped like hollow soccer balls.; 2. Advances in gene
therapy: First treatments attempted in humans. Defective cystic fibrosis genes
repaired in the test tube.; 3. Two more detectors join the search for elusive
particles called solar neutrinos.; 4. Genetically engineered hormone used to
stimulate milk production in cows is cleared as a human health risk, but still
