chemical receptor in their brain cells, supporting the idea that alcoholism
may be hereditary.; 2. Advances in gene therapy. See No. 2 above. (Only item
on both lists.); 3. Zebra mussels invade Great Lakes, clogging inlets and
pipelines.; 4. British researchers find genetic switch that determines if a
baby will be a boy or a girl.; 5. Physicists develop computer processor that
uses laser beams instead of electrons to carry information.; 6. Mathematicians
offer proof that it takes precisely seven shuffles to mix a deck of cards.; 7.
Oil spills continue at average levels -- proving the world has learned nothing
from the 1989 Exxon Valdez disaster.; 8. First AIDS death is traced back to an
ex-sailor in Manchester, England, in 1959.; 9. Space news: Hubble Space
Telescope disappoints, but Magellan sends back spectacular shots of Venus.;
